@page "/components/material-design"

<PageTitle>Material Design</PageTitle>

<W3Container Class="w3-padding-32">
    <h1>Material Design</h1>
    <DocPager PreviousHref="components/case-study" PreviousText="Case Study" NextHref="components/versions" NextText="Versions" />

    <p class="w3-large">W3.CSS presents Material Design as paper-like surfaces, realistic shadows, hover response, theme colors, app bars, lists, and cards.</p>
    <p>This page follows the same lesson shape and translates each section into lightweight Blazor components plus ordinary W3.CSS classes.</p>

    <DocExample Title="Material Design Basics" Description="Start with the paper-and-ink idea: flat content, layered surfaces, and visible depth." Code="@BasicsCode">
        <W3Grid Padding="true" Style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr)); align-items: stretch;">
            <W3Container Color="W3Color.LightGrey" Class="w3-padding-24">
                <W3Image Src="https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/img_material.png" Alt="Material Design layers" Loading="eager" Style="width:100%; max-height:220px; object-fit:contain;" />
            </W3Container>

            <W3Card Depth="W3CardDepth.Four" Round="W3Round.Medium" HeaderColor="W3Color.Indigo" HeaderClass="w3-text-white" BodyColor="W3Color.White" FooterClass="w3-padding-16" Class="w3-white w3-hover-shadow">
                <Header><h2 class="w3-large">Layered surface</h2></Header>
                <ChildContent>
                    <p>Use cards and shadows when content should feel raised above the page.</p>
                    <p>Keep the body simple so the shadow and action remain easy to read.</p>
                </ChildContent>
                <Footer>
                    <W3Button Color="W3Color.Indigo" TextColor="W3Color.White" Round="W3Round.Medium">Open surface</W3Button>
                </Footer>
            </W3Card>
        </W3Grid>
    </DocExample>

    <DocExample Title="Material Design Look Using W3.CSS" Description="The W3.CSS source page starts with a downloads panel. In Blazor, use a card, list rows, icons, and hover classes." Code="@DownloadsCode">
        <W3Card Depth="W3CardDepth.Four" Round="W3Round.Medium" HeaderColor="W3Color.BlueGrey" HeaderClass="w3-text-white" BodyColor="W3Color.White" Class="w3-white" Style="max-width: 620px;">
            <Header>
                <h2 class="w3-large">Downloads</h2>
            </Header>
            <ChildContent>
                <W3List Hoverable="true">
                    <li class="w3-padding-16">
                        <span class="w3-small w3-text-grey">Today</span>
                        <W3Button Class="w3-right" Round="W3Round.Medium" Border="true">X</W3Button>
                        <div class="w3-margin-top">
                            <W3Icon IconClass="fa fa-file-archive-o" TextColor="W3Color.BlueGrey" Class="w3-margin-right" />
                            email.zip
                        </div>
                        <div class="w3-small w3-text-grey">https://www.example.com/lib/email.zip</div>
                        <W3Button Color="W3Color.LightGrey" Round="W3Round.Medium" Class="w3-margin-top">Show in folder</W3Button>
                    </li>
                    <li class="w3-padding-16">
                        <span class="w3-small w3-text-grey">Yesterday</span>
                        <W3Button Class="w3-right" Round="W3Round.Medium" Border="true">X</W3Button>
                        <div class="w3-margin-top">
                            <W3Icon IconClass="fa fa-file-pdf-o" TextColor="W3Color.Red" Class="w3-margin-right" />
                            invoice.pdf
                        </div>
                        <div class="w3-small w3-text-grey">https://www.example.com/lib/invoice.pdf</div>
                        <W3Button Color="W3Color.LightGrey" Round="W3Round.Medium" Class="w3-margin-top">Show in folder</W3Button>
                    </li>
                </W3List>
            </ChildContent>
        </W3Card>
    </DocExample>

    <DocExample Title="Material Design Look With Color Themes" Description="Load a W3.CSS theme file, then compose themed headers, images, cards, and tags." Code="@ThemeCardsCode">
        <div class="w3-card-4 w3-white" style="max-width: 820px;">
            <W3Container Class="w3-theme w3-padding-16">
                <h2 class="w3-xlarge">Places to Visit</h2>
            </W3Container>
            <W3Image Src="https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/img_5terre.jpg" Alt="Cinque Terre coast" Loading="eager" Style="width:100%; max-height:260px; object-fit:cover;" />
            <W3Container Class="w3-padding-16">
                <h3 class="w3-large">Cinque Terre</h3>
                <p>Theme color gives the app frame a clear identity while the content remains plain and readable.</p>
            </W3Container>
            <W3Row Padding="true" Class="w3-padding-16">
                <W3Column Small="12" Medium="6">
                    <div class="w3-card w3-white w3-hover-shadow">
                        <W3Image Src="https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/img_monterosso.jpg" Alt="Monterosso" Loading="eager" Style="width:100%; height:150px; object-fit:cover;" />
                        <W3Container Class="w3-padding">
                            <h3 class="w3-large">Monterosso</h3>
                            <p>A raised content card with an image and a short description.</p>
                        </W3Container>
                    </div>
                </W3Column>
                <W3Column Small="12" Medium="6">
                    <div class="w3-card w3-white w3-hover-shadow">
                        <W3Image Src="https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/img_vernazza.jpg" Alt="Vernazza" Loading="eager" Style="width:100%; height:150px; object-fit:cover;" />
                        <W3Container Class="w3-padding">
                            <h3 class="w3-large">Vernazza</h3>
                            <p>Footer tags can add compact metadata without extra layout code.</p>
                            <span class="w3-tag w3-theme-l2 w3-round">Europe</span>
                            <span class="w3-tag w3-theme-l1 w3-round">Italy</span>
                        </W3Container>
                    </div>
                </W3Column>
            </W3Row>
        </div>
    </DocExample>

    <DocExample Title="Material Design Look With Navigation Bars" Description="The W3.CSS source separates status bars, toolbars, tab/search bars, and the combined app shell." Code="@NavigationCode">
        <div id="material-navigation" class="w3-white" style="max-width: 720px;">
            <h3 class="w3-large">Status Bar:</h3>
            <W3Container Class="w3-theme-d4 w3-right-align w3-small">
                12:30
            </W3Container>

            <h3 class="w3-large">Toolbar:</h3>
            <W3Bar Class="w3-theme">
                <W3BarItem Button="false"><strong>Title</strong></W3BarItem>
                <W3BarItem Class="w3-right"><W3Icon IconClass="fa fa-search" /> Search</W3BarItem>
            </W3Bar>

            <h3 class="w3-large">Tab Bar / Search Bar:</h3>
            <W3Bar Class="w3-theme-l1">
                <W3BarItem Href="components/material-design#material-navigation" Mobile="true">Link 1</W3BarItem>
                <W3BarItem Href="components/material-design#material-navigation" Mobile="true">Link 2</W3BarItem>
                <W3BarItem Href="components/material-design#material-navigation" Mobile="true">Link 3</W3BarItem>
                <W3BarItem Href="components/material-design#material-navigation" Mobile="true">Link 4</W3BarItem>
            </W3Bar>

            <h3 class="w3-large">All Together Now:</h3>
            <div class="w3-border">
                <W3Container Class="w3-theme-d4 w3-right-align w3-small">12:30</W3Container>
                <W3Bar Class="w3-theme">
                    <W3BarItem Button="false"><strong>Title</strong></W3BarItem>
                    <W3BarItem Class="w3-right"><W3Icon IconClass="fa fa-ellipsis-v" /></W3BarItem>
                </W3Bar>
                <W3Bar Class="w3-theme-l1">
                    <W3BarItem Href="components/material-design#material-navigation" Mobile="true">Link 1</W3BarItem>
                    <W3BarItem Href="components/material-design#material-navigation" Mobile="true">Link 2</W3BarItem>
                    <W3BarItem Href="components/material-design#material-navigation" Mobile="true">Link 3</W3BarItem>
                    <W3BarItem Href="components/material-design#material-navigation" Mobile="true">Link 4</W3BarItem>
                </W3Bar>
                <W3Container Class="w3-padding-24">
                    <p>The bars stay stylesheet-driven, and any interactive actions can use normal Blazor callbacks.</p>
                </W3Container>
            </div>
        </div>
    </DocExample>

    <DocExample Title="Material Design Look With Colorful Cards" Description="Use category color and images for the final card pattern from the W3.CSS source page." Code="@ColorfulCardsCode">
        <W3Grid Padding="true" Style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));">
            <div class="w3-card-4 w3-white w3-hover-shadow">
                <W3Container Color="W3Color.Crimson" TextColor="W3Color.White" Class="w3-center">
                    <h2 class="w3-large">Sport</h2>
                </W3Container>
                <W3Image Src="https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/img_md_sport.jpg" Alt="Sport" Loading="eager" Style="width:100%; height:160px; object-fit:cover;" />
            </div>

            <div class="w3-card-4 w3-white w3-hover-shadow">
                <W3Container Color="W3Color.Cobalt" TextColor="W3Color.White" Class="w3-center">
                    <h2 class="w3-large">News</h2>
                </W3Container>
                <W3Image Src="https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/img_md_globe.jpg" Alt="News" Loading="eager" Style="width:100%; height:160px; object-fit:cover;" />
            </div>

            <div class="w3-card-4 w3-white w3-hover-shadow">
                <W3Container Color="W3Color.Emerald" TextColor="W3Color.White" Class="w3-center">
                    <h2 class="w3-large">Music</h2>
                </W3Container>
                <W3Image Src="https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/img_md_music.jpg" Alt="Music" Loading="eager" Style="width:100%; height:160px; object-fit:cover;" />
            </div>
        </W3Grid>
    </DocExample>

    <section class="doc-section">
        <h2>Usage Reference</h2>
        <W3Table Striped="true" Bordered="true" Responsive="true" Class="doc-reference-table">
            <thead>
                <tr><th>Source section</th><th>Use</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr><td>Material Design</td><td>`W3Image`, `W3Card.Depth`, `W3Round`, and `w3-hover-shadow`</td><td>Use depth to show hierarchy, not decoration.</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Downloads panel</td><td>`W3Card`, `W3List`, `W3Icon`, `W3Button`, and utility classes</td><td>Rows can include labels, metadata, and compact actions.</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Color themes</td><td>`w3-theme-*` classes loaded by the consuming app</td><td>Theme files stay app-owned and flow through `Class`.</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Navigation bars</td><td>`W3Bar`, `W3BarItem`, `W3Container`, and icons</td><td>Use routed fragments for same-page links under Blazor routing.</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Colorful cards</td><td>`W3Container`, `W3Image`, typed colors, and card utility classes</td><td>Use color to identify content categories.</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Images and icons</td><td>`W3Image` and `W3Icon`</td><td>The docs site loads the same support assets used by these examples.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </W3Table>
    </section>

    <section class="doc-section">
        <h2>Related W3.CSS</h2>
        <p><NavLink href="components/card">Card component</NavLink></p>
        <p><NavLink href="components/effects">Effects utility</NavLink></p>
        <p><NavLink href="components/colors">Colors guidance</NavLink></p>
        <p><NavLink href="components/color-schemes">Color Schemes guidance</NavLink></p>
        <p><NavLink href="components/case-study">Case Study guidance</NavLink></p>
        <p><NavLink href="components/versions">Versions guidance</NavLink></p>
        <p><a href="https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/w3css_material.asp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">W3.CSS Material Design</a></p>
        <p><a href="https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/w3css_color_themes.asp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">W3.CSS Color Themes</a></p>
        <p><a href="https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/w3css_color_material.asp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">W3.CSS Material Colors</a></p>
        <p><a href="https://m3.material.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Material Design</a></p>
    </section>

    <DocPager PreviousHref="components/case-study" PreviousText="Case Study" NextHref="components/versions" NextText="Versions" />
</W3Container>

